--
-- v2.5 ships an upgraded visual layer on top of the v2.0 API.  The
-- public surface (CreateWindow / CreateTab / CreateButton / CreateToggle
-- / CreateSlider / CreateDropdown / CreateInput / CreateColorPicker /
-- CreateKeybind / CreateSection / CreateLabel / CreateParagraph /
-- Notify / LoadConfiguration / SetTheme / Toggle / Show / Hide /
-- SetToggleKeybind) is byte-for-byte identical to v2.0, so existing
-- scripts continue to load without modification:
--
--   local Aquafield = loadstring(game:HttpGet('.../Aquafield'))()
--   local Window = Aquafield:CreateWindow({ Name = '...', Theme='Ocean' })
--
-- What is new under the hood:
--   * Theme catalogue trimmed to 3 hand-tuned palettes: Ocean,
--     MatrixGreen, Crimson.  The legacy theme names (Amethyst,
--     Sunset, Midnight, Forest, Cyber, Aurora, Mono) still resolve
--     to one of the 3 cores via alias so legacy configs do not
--     hard-error when loaded.
--   * Every theme now publishes a full gradient contract
--     (BgGradientA/B/C, AccentA/B/C, HaloHue, ShimmerHue, GlowHue,
--     ParticleHue) consumed by the FX engine.
--   * FX engine: a single RunService.Heartbeat connection drives
--     all motion in the library through a small layer registry.
--     Adding a new effect is a one-liner.
--   * Topbar buttons (close / minimize / hide) replaced the
--     garbled UTF-8 glyphs with lucide-roblox ImageButton assets,
--     plus a unicode fallback layer underneath for executors that
--     cannot stream image content.
--   * Multi-layer animated stack per window: themed rotating
--     gradient, breathing accent halo, shimmer sweep, drifting
--     accent orb, particle field.
